  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act (in the United States)\n- Proceeds of Crime legislation\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Record-keeping obligations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Financial penalties\n- Regulatory sanctions\n\n5. Investigative Approaches\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Cross-border cooperation\n- Sophisticated tracking technologies\n- Forensic accounting techniques\n\n6. Regulatory Compliance\n- Financial institutions must implement compliance programs\n- Regular risk assessments\n- Staff training\n- Internal monitoring systems\n\n7. Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining global financial system integrity.",
